	LSC Lithium Corporation - About - Management



































Skip to main content












toggle menu






Search Site

































Home»About»Management
        






Our management team is comprised of talented individuals with a wealth of industry experience and the operating know-how that is fundamental to the success of LSC.







, Chairman, President and Chief Executive Officer







Wayne Richardson

Wayne Richardson has had a career in strategic business development at a senior management level in domestic and international markets, including a track record of successful management of turnaround, growth and start-up companies.Having a solid understanding of fundamental business drivers, his recycling, service delivery, energy storage and automotive industry experience combined with his sales and marketing knowledge has enabled him to conceptualize, implement and deliver complex projects. In particular he has been a leader in identifying and delivering market changing business models.







, Chief Financial Officer







Lincoln Greenidge

Lincoln Greenidge is a Canadian Chartered Professional Accountant who has had various Finance roles within industries such as Commercial Banking, High Technology, Life Sciences, Dry Food Products, and Mining over the past two decades. Mr. Greenidge is the VP, Finance and Corporate Controller of Enirgi Group and the Chief Financial Officer of LeadFX Inc. Prior to joining Enirgi Group, he was Corporate Controller of HudBay Minerals and IAMGOLD leading the creation and development of their Global Finance teams.







, Chief Operating Officer







Carlos Galli

Carlos Galli is an Industrial Engineer graduated from the School of Engineering - University of Buenos Aires, in 2001. He has been working with ADY Resources (a subsidiary of Enirgi Group) since 2010, first as Industrial Manager and then as General Manager of Operations. Mr. Galli has participated in the construction and management of a safe and sustainable lithium carbonate plant operation in the Puna plateau of Argentina, which delivered product to 5 countries. Among his past work experiences, he was an Industrial Segments Manager in SKF Latin America, and a Process Technology Business Manager in Alfa Laval; among others.







, Vice President, Investor Relations and Corporate Communications







Jessica Helm

Jessica Helm has over a decade of experience in Corporate Communications and Investor Relations, Institutional Trading, and Equity Capital Markets. Ms. Helm began her career in Equity Capital Markets where she worked for Macquarie Bank and a leading independent investment dealer that was acquired by a large Canadian Bank. Prior to joining Enirgi Group in 2013, Jessica worked as an Institutional Equity Sales Trader at CIBC World Markets in Toronto where she was responsible for executing trades of behalf of institutional clients. Jessica holds a Bachelor of Arts (Honours Political Science and Honours Applied Studies) and a Specialization in International Trade from the University of Waterloo.







, Vice President, Legal and Corporate Secretary







D'Arcy Doherty

D’Arcy Doherty is the VP, Legal and General Counsel of Enirgi Group Corporation and LeadFX Inc. He is a former partner with Gowling Lafleur Henderson LLP (now Gowling WLG), one of Canada’s largest law firms, where he worked with public mining companies focusing on corporate and securities law. Mr. Doherty holds a Bachelor of Arts from McGill University, a Bachelor of Laws from the University of Victoria and a Master of Laws (Securities Law) from Osgoode Hall Law School. D’Arcy is a member of the Ontario bar.
























